18/07/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- President Alfred Moisiu decided Thursday (17 July) to hold local elections on 12 October.
The Central Electoral Commission has already kicked off preparations.
Special attention is being paid to the voter registration list, which has been a point of contention in the past.
Meanwhile, top officials met with visiting NATO Secretary General George Robertson on Thursday, reiterating Albania's commitment to join the Alliance.
Robertson told Moisiu the country could rely on continued assistance and support from NATO.
(Albanian Daily News - 17/07/03)
